definition: to pass (sth) on (to sb else)/to transfer sb (to another hospital etc)
to revolve/to turn/to circle about/to walk about/classifier for revolutions (per minute etc): revs, rpm/classifier for repeated actions
to turn/to change direction/to transfer/to forward (mail)
to deliver/to carry/to give (as a present)/to present (with)/to see off/to send

pinyin: dang4 an4 zhuan3 song4 cun2 qu3 ji2 guan3 li3

sentences.english: Datagrams cannot always be forwarded to their destinations.
sentences.chinese: 資料元經常無法轉送到它們的目的地。

sentences.english: For example, aggregated details of individual purchasing transactions are transferred to the general ledger system.
sentences.chinese: 各個採購異動的組成細節可以轉送到總帳系統。

sentences.english: Channel requests relay information such as the exit code of a server-side process.
sentences.chinese: 通道請求轉送信息，比如服務器端流程的退出代碼。

sentences.english: He treasures the things I buy for him, and never gives them to other people.
sentences.chinese: 我買給他的東西都合他心，不轉送他人。

sentences.english: Letters and Complaints Bureau if it is only transferred to the State, who come to supervise it?
sentences.chinese: 國家信訪局如果只是轉送，誰又來督辦呢？

sentences.english: The requests for transfers were channeled through the personnel office.
sentences.chinese: 請求調動的申請書轉送到了人事部門。

sentences.english: He was transferred to a field hospital at a nearby plantation to recover.
sentences.chinese: 他被轉送到種植園附近一家戰地醫院裏康復。

sentences.english: Tse was transferred to the intensive care unit on April 15 after her condition deteriorated.
sentences.chinese: 謝醫生於四月十五日病情惡化，轉送深切治療部。

sentences.english: Follows tong received our Ye sent flowers, the flowers the forwarding to the colleagues.
sentences.chinese: 妁彤收到雋燁送來的鮮花，把花轉送予同事。

sentences.english: They said the remaining two miners required more attention and were being transferred to other hospitals.
sentences.chinese: 院方表示兩名礦工需要進一步觀察並轉送到其他醫院。

sentences.english: Therefore please let us have full details of your products so that we can pass on the information.
sentences.chinese: 故請寄來貴公司產品的詳細資料，以便轉送。

definition: to refer sb to an agency (or hospital etc)/referral
(Tw) medical checkup/physical examination (abbr. for 健康檢查|健康检查[jian4 kang1 jian3 cha2])
to pass on to sb/to carry and give to sb else
see 體格檢查|体格检查[ti3 ge2 jian3 cha2]
to disappear without trace/to vanish all of a sudden/to spread fast/to spread like wildfire
to visit (a patient, prisoner etc)/to look inquiringly
